      KIC Events Disability Accommodation Policy
    </h2>
    <div class="content bod-text">
      <p>
        At KIC Events, we are committed to fostering an inclusive, accessible, and welcoming environment for all attendees. We recognize that individuals with disabilities may require accommodations, including the use of personal devices to monitor health conditions, navigate spaces, or assist with communication.  In accordance with the ADA, we provide Reasonable Accommodations (RA) for those who require them.
      </p>
      <p class="h5">
        Use of Phones & Electronic Devices for Accessibility
      </p>
      <p>
        While our event maintains a no-electronic devices/phones policy in event spaces to protect privacy and create a distraction-free environment, we fully acknowledge that some attendees rely on their phones or other electronic devices as medical or accessibility tools. Devices used for these purposes are exempt from the no-phone policy when required for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Monitoring health conditions (e.g., blood glucose monitors, heart rate monitors, seizure alert systems)</li>
        <li>Communication assistance (e.g., speech-to-text apps, AAC devices)</li>
        <li>Navigation and mobility support (e.g., screen readers, GPS, visual or auditory aids)</li>
        <li>Other disability-related needs as required by the attendee</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="h5">
        Requesting an Accommodation
      </p>
      <p>
        In accordance with the ADA, we provide Reasonable Accommodations (RA) for those who require them.  If you require the use of a phone or other device in the event space for disability-related reasons, you do not need to disclose specific medical details, but we ask that you:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Inform event staff or a designated Accessibility Coordinator upon arrival or at check-in.</li>
        <li>A RA Sticker will be received by attendees to place on their event badge.</li>
        <li>Ensure that usage is discreet and solely for accessibility purposes.</li>
        <li>Use vibrate/silent mode to minimize disruption.</li>
        <li>Videos and photos are not allowed to maintain event and attendee privacy.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="h5">
        Additional Accommodations
      </p>
      <p>
        We strive to accommodate additional accessibility needs, including but not limited to:
      </p>
